Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with semantic interpretation of noun-noun compounds using neural classification models. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses transfer and multi-task learning techniques to improve the performance of the classification model. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as the paper discusses techniques to improve the accuracy of a classifier on a skewed distribution of relations. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses neural networks for the classification task.
